The President held a meeting with his national security team to discuss the threat of foreign terrorist fighters to the US and other nations. The President will chair a United Nations Security Council summit next week to address this threat. Participants in the meeting included the Vice President, Secretary of Defense, Attorney General, Secretary of Homeland Security, White House Chief of Staff, Counselor to the President, National Security Advisor, US Permanent Representative to the United Nations, White House Counsel, Director of National Intelligence, Director of the Central Intelligence Agency, Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation, Director of the National Counterterrorism Center, Director of the National Security Agency, Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, Deputy National Security Advisor, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Executive Secretary and Chief of Staff of the National Security Council, Acting National Security Advisor to the Vice President, Deputy Assistant to the President for Homeland Security.